Motive
Hogue was suspected in two robberies in which $1.2 million was stolen. It was likely he thought he was about to be arrested as four other policemen were being questioned after attempting to spend the cancelled money to week prior to his familicide.
Leonard Raymond Hogue was a Canadian police officer who killed his wife and six children in Coquitlam, BC, Canada on April 20th, 1965, before committing suicide.[1]
Victims[]
Vera Irene Hogue, 33, his wife
Larry Hogue, 13, his son
Noreen Hogue, 12, his daughter
Raymond Hogue, 8, his son
Clifford Hogue, 6, his son
Darlene Hogue, 4, his daughter
Richard Hogue, 3, his son
